'''Abdukodir Khikmatzhon ugli Khusanov'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce89/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |title=FIFA U-20 World Cup Argentina 2023 SQUAD LIST: Uzbekistan (UZB) |publisher=FIFA |page=24 |date=22 May 2023 |access-date=29 May 2023 |archive-date=19 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230519182011/https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce89/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |url-status=live }}</ref>{{efn|{{langx|ru|Абдукодир Хикматжон угли Хусанов}}<ref>{{cite web |date=25 August 2023 |title=О награждении в связи с тридцать второй годовщиной независимости Республики Узбекистан группы спортсменов и тренеров, добившихся высоких результатов |trans-title=On awarding a group of athletes and coaches who have achieved high results on the occasion of the thirty-second anniversary of the independence of the Republic of Uzbekistan |url=https://president.uz/ru/lists/view/6617 |url-status=live |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=17 August 2025 |website=[[President of Uzbekistan|President of the Republic of Uzbekistan]] |language=ru}}</ref>}} ({{langx|uz|Abduqodir Xikmatjon o‘g‘li Xusanov}};<ref name="president.uz" /> born 29 February 2004) is an Uzbek professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] and [[right-back]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/abdukodir-khusanov-signing-manchester-city-63872982 |title= City complete signing of Uzbek defender Khusanov|publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=20 January 2025 |access-date=20 January 2025}}</ref>

Graduating from the youth setup of Bunyodkor, Khusanov started his career in Belarus with [[FC Energetik-BGU Minsk|Energetik-BGU]] in 2022, where he played for one and a half seasons before his transfer to French side [[RC Lens|Lens]] in 2023. While at Lens, he became the first Uzbek to play in Ligue 1, and a key player for the club before joining Manchester City in 2025, making history by becoming the first Uzbek player in the English Premier League.<ref name="PL">{{cite news |date=24 January 2025 |title=Khusanov makes Uzbekistan the Premier League's 126th nation |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3960097 |access-date=29 January 2025 |publisher=Premier League |archive-date=10 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240410071352/https://www.premierleague.com/news/3960097 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Abdukodir is an Uzbekistan international, having represented the country from under-17 age group onwards. He earned a senior call-up in 2023, representing them at the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].

==Club career==
===Early years===
Born in [[Tashkent]], Khusanov played for the youth teams of Uzbek club [[Bunyodkor]] up to the age of 18.{{Citation needed|date=April 2025}}

===Energetik-BGU===
In March 2022, Khusanov moved to Belarusian club [[FC Energetik-BGU Minsk|Energetik-BGU]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://energetikbgu.by/2022/03/17/%D0%B0%D0%B1%D0%B4%D1%83%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%B4%D1%8B%D1%80-%D1%85%D1%83%D1%81%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%B2-%D1%8D%D0%BD%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B3%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B5-%D0%B1%D0%B3%D1%83/ |title=Абдукадыр Хусанов в "Энергетике"-БГУ |work=«РЦОР по футболу БГУ» |date=17 March 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=25 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220925143737/http://energetikbgu.by/2022/03/17/%D0%B0%D0%B1%D0%B4%D1%83%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%B4%D1%8B%D1%80-%D1%85%D1%83%D1%81%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%B2-%D1%8D%D0%BD%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B3%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B5-%D0%B1%D0%B3%D1%83/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 19 March in a match against [[FC Vitebsk|Vitebsk]], starting and playing the entire match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/03/19/belarus/premier-league/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/fc-vitebsk/3752893/ |title=Energetyk-BGU vs. Vitebsk |language=en |website=Soccerway |date=19 March 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=22 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220322115232/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/03/19/belarus/premier-league/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/fc-vitebsk/3752893/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://football.by/news/162299.html |title=Высшая лига, 1 тур. "Энергетик-БГУ" выиграл у "Витебска" |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=26 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220326204326/https://football.by/news/162299.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Khusanov scored his first goal on 2 May, in a match against [[FC Neman|Neman Grodno]], where he also gave two assists.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/05/02/belarus/premier-league/fc-neman-grodno/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/3753308/ |title=Neman Grodno vs. Energetyk-BGU |language=en |website=Soccerway |date=2 May 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=3 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220503170347/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/05/02/belarus/premier-league/fc-neman-grodno/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/3753308/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In August, Khusanov was included in the list of the most promising players in the world according to the International Center for Sports Research.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://energetikbgu.by/2022/08/30/%D0%B0%D0%B1%D0%B4%D1%83%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%80-%D1%85%D1%83%D1%81%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%B2-%D1%81%D0%BF%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B5-%D1%81%D0%B0%D0%BC%D1%8B%D1%85-%D0%BF%D0%B5%D1%80%D1%81/ |title=Абдукодир Хусанов в списке самых перспективных игроков мира! |language=ru |website=energetikbgu.by |date=30 August 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=9 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220909095831/http://energetikbgu.by/2022/08/30/%D0%B0%D0%B1%D0%B4%D1%83%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%80-%D1%85%D1%83%D1%81%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%B2-%D1%81%D0%BF%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B5-%D1%81%D0%B0%D0%BC%D1%8B%D1%85-%D0%BF%D0%B5%D1%80%D1%81/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> At the end of the season, his club finished as the runners-up of the [[2022 Belarusian Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://energetikbgu.by/2022/11/13/%D1%83-%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%81-%D1%81%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%B1%D1%80%D0%BE/ |title=У нас серебро! |language=ru |website=energetikbgu.by |date=13 November 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=23 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323070435/http://energetikbgu.by/2022/11/13/%d1%83-%d0%bd%d0%b0%d1%81-%d1%81%d0%b5%d1%80%d0%b5%d0%b1%d1%80%d0%be/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> He got into the symbolic team of the championship.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football.by/news/169448 |title=Четверо из "Энергетика-БГУ", трое из БАТЭ, двое — чемпионы страны. Символическая сборная высшей лиги |language=ru |website=football.by |date=15 November 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115132213/https://football.by/news/169448 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In December 2022, Energetik-BGU reported that Khusanov would continue to play at the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football.by/news/170298 |title=На сегодня наряд: уборка снега — тридцать человек! "Энергетик-БГУ" начал подготовку к сезону |language=ru |website=football.by |date=8 December 2022 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=9 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221209182155/https://football.by/news/170298 |url-status=live }}</ref> His first match of the [[2023 Belarusian Premier League|new season]] was on 2 April 2023 against [[BATE Borisov]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/04/02/belarus/premier-league/fc-bate-borisov/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/4041997/ |title=BATE vs. Energetyk-BGU |website=Soccerway |date=2 April 2023 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=2 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230402203728/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/04/02/belarus/premier-league/fc-bate-borisov/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/4041997/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He got into the symbolic team of the second round of the [[Belarusian Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football.by/news/173440 |title=Морозов, Хусанов и Калачев в сборной 2-го тура высшей лиги по версии Football.by |language=ru |website=football.by |date=3 April 2023 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=4 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404120758/https://football.by/news/173440 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 April, Khusanov scored his first goal of the season in a match against [[FC Shakhtyor Soligorsk|Shakhtyor Soligorsk]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/04/23/belarus/premier-league/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/fc-shakhtyor-soligorsk/4042014/ |title=Energetyk-BGU vs. Shakhtyor Soligorsk |website=Soccerway |date=23 April 2023 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=23 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423173200/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/04/23/belarus/premier-league/fc-zvezda-bgu-minsk/fc-shakhtyor-soligorsk/4042014/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Three days later, he was included in the list of the most promising players under the age of 20, where he took 15th place among [[centre-back]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-observatory.com/IMG/sites/b5wp/2022/wp419/en/ |title=World ranking of the 200 most promising youngsters |website=football-observatory.com |date=26 April 2023 |access-date=15 June 2023 |archive-date=26 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426181853/https://football-observatory.com/IMG/sites/b5wp/2022/wp419/en/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Lens===
[[File:Lens - Torino FC (02-08-2023) 58.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Khusanov with [[RC Lens|Lens]] in 2023]]
On 24 July 2023, Khusanov signed with [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Lens|Lens]] on a four-year contract.<ref name="Mercato">[https://www.rclens.fr/fr/news/mercato-rclens-arrivee-abdukodir-khusanov-20230724 Abdukodir Khusanov, talent brut venu d'Asie] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724152516/https://www.rclens.fr/fr/news/mercato-rclens-arrivee-abdukodir-khusanov-20230724 |date=24 July 2023 }}, [[RC Lens]], sur ''rclens.fr'', 24 July 2023</ref> He made his debut for the club on 16 September in a 1–0 home loss against [[FC Metz|Metz]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Saison 2023–2024 championnat |url=https://www.rclens.fr/fr/match/saison-2023-2024-championnat-ligue1-uber-eats-journee-5-lens-metz |website=RC Lens |access-date=23 December 2024}}</ref> becoming the first Uzbek player to play in [[Ligue 1]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Comment Abdukodir Khusanov, l'inconnu d'Ouzbékistan, séduit Lens |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Comment-abdukodir-khusanov-l-inconnu-d-ouzbekistan-seduit-lens/1424039 |website=L’Equipe |access-date=23 December 2024}}</ref> On 29 November, Khusanov played his first UEFA club competition game, a 6–0 [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League group stage|UEFA Champions League group stage]] defeat against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]. At 19 years and 9 months old, he became the youngest Uzbek to play in the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |title=History: Arsenal 6–0 Lens |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039157/ |publisher=UEFA |access-date=23 December 2024}}</ref>

His final match with Lens took place on 22 December 2024 in the [[2024–25 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]] against [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]], marking his debut as the first Uzbek player to participate in the competition. The match ended in a 1–1 draw, with Lens ultimately eliminated after a penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite web |title=En sang mais en or : Khusanov, le trésor de la défense du RC Lens |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/En-sang-mais-en-or-khusanov-le-tresor-de-la-defense-du-rc-lens/1528282 |website=L’Equipe |access-date=21 January 2025 |archive-date=4 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250104015306/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/En-sang-mais-en-or-khusanov-le-tresor-de-la-defense-du-rc-lens/1528282 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Manchester City===
On 20 January 2025, Khusanov became the first Uzbek player to sign for a [[Premier League]] club, joining [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on a four-and-a-half-year deal, on a reported initial fee of €40&nbsp;million,<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 January 2025 |title=Man City sign Uzbekistan defender Khusanov from Lens |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/man-city-sign-uzbekistan-defender-182630820.html#:~:text=Manchester%20City%20on%20Monday%20announced,year%20deal%20at%20the%20Etihad. |access-date=2025-01-25 |website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/abdukodir-khusanov-signing-manchester-city-63872982 |title= City complete signing of Uzbek defender Khusanov |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=20 January 2025 |access-date=20 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=20 January 2025 |title=Man City signs 20-year-old Khusanov for $41.5 million to kick off expected January spending spree |url=https://apnews.com/article/khusanov-man-city-b8c4b97fa830b2aeb2b53552364ee17a |access-date=2025-01-25 |website=AP News |archive-date=25 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250125185239/https://apnews.com/article/khusanov-man-city-b8c4b97fa830b2aeb2b53552364ee17a |url-status=live }}</ref> and on 25 January, he made his debut against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3960097 |title=Khusanov makes Uzbekistan the Premier League's 126th nation |publisher=Premier League |date=24 January 2025 |access-date=1 March 2025 |archive-date=10 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240410071352/https://www.premierleague.com/news/3960097 |url-status=live }}</ref> 
<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 January 2025 |title=Man City 3–1 Chelsea: Premier League champions recover from Abdukodir Khusanov's nightmare start |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c5yve69gmr9o |access-date=26 February 2025 |website=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> On 8 February 2025, Khusanov, deflecting into the net a shot by teammate [[Rico Lewis]], scored his first goal for Manchester City in a [[2024-25 FA Cup#Fourth round|fourth round]] 1–2 away victory over [[EFL League One|third-tier]] side [[Leyton Orient F.C.|Leyton Orient]], his first [[FA Cup]] game.<ref>{{cite news |title=FA Cup fourth round: Man City come from behind to beat Leyton Orient |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/ce9n4mg7kpkt |first=Simon |last=Stone |work=BBC Sport|access-date=26 February 2026|archive-date=8 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250208131841/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/ce9n4mg7kpkt |date=8 February 2025 }}</ref>

A year later, in January 2026, Guardiola expressed his satisfaction with "Khusa," whose progress, he said, showed he's a "top signing."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/pep-guardiola-on-abdukodir-khusanov-newcastle-v-manchester-city-pre-match-embargo-63903834|title=Guardiola delighted with 'top signing' Khusanov's City progress |last=Leigh  |first=Neil  |date=12 January 2026 |website=Manchester City FC |access-date=26 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Khusanov played for the [[Uzbekistan national under-17 football team|Uzbekistan under-17 national team]]. In June 2022, he made his debut for the [[Uzbekistan national under-19 football team|Uzbekistan under-19 team]], playing two friendly matches against [[Belarus national under-19 football team|Belarus]]. In September 2022, he was called up to the [[Uzbekistan national under-17 football team|Uzbekistan under-20 team]], for which he played two full matches against [[Slovakia national under-17 football team|Slovakia]].

====U20 team====
In March 2023, Khusanov joined the Uzbekistan U20 squad for the [[2023 AFC U-20 Asian Cup|AFC U-20 Asian Cup]]. His first tournament match was on 1 March 2023, against [[Syria national under-20 football team|Syria]]. The team topped their group, advancing to the knockout stage. On 11 March 2023, Khusanov helped the team defeat [[Australia men's national under-20 soccer team|Australia]] in a penalty shoot-out in the quarter-finals, thus securing a spot in the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]. In their semi-final on 15 March 2023, Uzbekistan defeated [[South Korea national under-20 football team|South Korea]] in another penalty shoot-out. The team then claimed the championship title by defeating [[Iraq national under-20 football team|Iraq]] in the final on 18 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/matches/afc-u20-asian-cup/2023/2359246 |title=Uzbekistan 1–0 Iraq |website=AFC |date=18 March 2023 }}</ref>

In May 2023, Khusanov was called up to the Uzbekistan U20 team for the FIFA U-20 World Cup. His first match in the tournament was on 20 May 2023, against [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina]]. After finishing second in their group, the team advanced to the knockout stage, where they were eliminated by [[Israel national under-19 football team|Israel]] in the round of 16 on 30 May 2023.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/match-centre/match/104/284700/284706/400016629 |title=Uzbekistan 0–1 Israel |publisher=FIFA |date=30 May 2023 |access-date=11 January 2025 |archive-date=11 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250111005437/https://www.fifa.com/en/match-centre/match/104/284700/284706/400016629 |url-status=live }}</ref> Throughout the tournament, Khusanov was a key player, playing every match in full.

====U23 team====
[[File:Uzbekistan vs. Spain, 2024 Summer Olympic men's association football, 2024-07-24 (260).jpg|thumb|Uzbekistan vs. Spain, 2024 Summer Olympics, [[Parc des Princes]], Paris.]]
In September 2023, Khusanov joined the [[Uzbekistan national under-23 football team|Uzbekistan U23 team]] for the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualification|AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualifiers]]. He debuted on 6 September 2023, in a match against [[Afghanistan national under-23 football team|Afghanistan]]. Khusanov provided his first assist for the under-23 team on 12 September 2023, in a match against [[Iran national under-23 football team|Iran]], which helped secure a narrow victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2023-09-12/uzbekistan-u23-vs-ir-iran-u23/3005658/ |title=Uzbekistan U23 1–0 IR Iran U23 |website=Global Sports Archive |date=12 September 2023 |access-date=11 January 2025 |archive-date=11 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250111005437/https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2023-09-12/uzbekistan-u23-vs-ir-iran-u23/3005658/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In April 2024, Khusanov was part of the Uzbekistan U23 squad for the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup|AFC U-23 Asian Cup]]. He played his first match on 23 April 2024 against [[Vietnam national under-23 football team|Vietnam]], starting in the line-up. The team reached the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup final|final]], where they lost to [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]] on 3 May 2024; however, Khusanov did not take part in the final match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/matches/afc-u23-asian-cup/2024/2414124 |title=Japan 1–0 Uzbekistan |website=AFC |date=3 May 2024 }}</ref>

===Senior===
[[File:Iran v Uzbekistan 2-2, 25 March 2025, Azadi Stadium, World Cup 2026 qualifier 8.jpg|thumb|Khusanov with the #2 shirt]]
In June 2023, Khusanov received a call-up to the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan senior national team]] to participate in the [[2023 CAFA Nations Cup|CAFA Nations Cup]]. On 11 June, he made his international debut against [[Oman national football team|Oman]], replacing [[Farrukh Sayfiev]] in the 83rd minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/36882/Uzbekistan_Oman.html |title=Uzbekistan vs. Oman |website=National Football Teams |date=11 June 2023 }}</ref> Together with the team, Khusanov reached the CAFA Nations Cup final, securing first place in the group stage. He ultimately became a silver medalist in the tournament, as the team lost to [[Iran national football team|Iran]] in the final on 20 June, where Khusanov spent the entire match on the bench.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2023-06-20/uzbekistan-vs-ir-iran/3006428/ |title=Match Report of Uzbekistan vs IR Iran – 2023-06-20 – CAFA Nations Cup – Global Sports Archive |access-date=16 January 2025 |archive-date=16 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250116101426/https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2023-06-20/uzbekistan-vs-ir-iran/3006428/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In January 2024, Khusanov travelled with the national team to the main stage of the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]]. His first match in the tournament took place on 13 January 2024, against [[Syria national football team|Syria]], where he started in the line-up and received a yellow card.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://assets.the-afc.com/2023_AFC_Asian_Cup/Downloads/Post_Match/MD1/M04-UZB-v-SYR.pdf |title=Uzbekistan 0–0 Syria |website=AFC |date=13 January 2024 |access-date=11 January 2025 |archive-date=11 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250111005438/https://assets.the-afc.com/2023_AFC_Asian_Cup/Downloads/Post_Match/MD1/M04-UZB-v-SYR.pdf |url-status=live }}</ref> By the end of the group stage, Khusanov and the team secured second place in the group and advanced to the knockout stage. Together with the team, he reached the quarter-finals, where Uzbekistan were eliminated by [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] on 3 February in a penalty shoot-out, thus concluding their tournament run.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/qatar-edge-uzbekistan-penalties-set-up-asian-cup-semi-final-with-iran-2024-02-03/ |title=Qatar edge Uzbekistan on penalties to set up Asian Cup semi-final with Iran |website=Reuters |date=3 February 2024 |access-date=11 January 2025 |archive-date=11 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240211215240/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/qatar-edge-uzbekistan-penalties-set-up-asian-cup-semi-final-with-iran-2024-02-03/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 5 June 2025, his defensive performance saw Uzbekistan qualify for the [[FIFA World Cup]] for the first time in their history, following a 0–0 draw against the [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]] in the 9th matchday of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round#Group A|Asian qualifiers]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=He |first=Fred |date=6 June 2025 |title=Rising Uzbekistan secure soccer World Cup debut, first ever Central Asian nation to qualify |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2025/06/06/sport/uzbekistan-uae-world-cup-qualifiers-soccer-intl-hnk |access-date=8 June 2025 |publisher=CNN}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Khusanov is the son of [[Khikmat Khashimov]] (also transliterated as Hikmat Hoshimov), who had a brief stint as a professional football player with [[PFK Metallurg Bekabad]].<ref name="Daryo">{{cite web |url=https://daryo.uz/2024/12/25/agressiv-va-intizomli-qanday-qilib-20-yoshli-abduqodir-husanov-yevropa-klublarining-eng-asosiy-maqsadi-bolib-qoldi |title=Tajovuzkor va intizomli: qanday qilib 20 yoshli Abduqodir Husanov Yevropa klublarining eng asosiy maqsadi boʻlib qoldi?|website=Daryo |access-date=29 January 2025 |language=Uzbek |date=25 December 2024}}</ref> "Abduqodir" is a common Uzbek name of Arabic origin and means "servant of the Almighty".<ref name="Campbell">{{cite web |last1=Campbell |first1=Jordan |title=Abdukodir Khusanov's tough beginning to life in the Premier League: How soon is too soon to start? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6089280/2025/01/28/khusanov-man-city-debut-chelsea/ |website=The Athletic |access-date=29 January 2025 |date=28 January 2025}}</ref>

In May 2025, Khusanov got married; the wedding, in Uzbek traditions, took place in Tashkent.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Тен |first=Александр |date=2025-05-29 |title=Абдукодир Хусанов женился — видео |url=https://uz.kursiv.media/2025-05-29/abdukodir-husanov-zhenilsya-foto-i-video/ |access-date=2025-06-13 |website=Kursiv Media Узбекистан |language=ru}}</ref>

Named to the Uzbekistan national team squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://t.me/uzpfl/77948|title=UzPFL|website=Telegram|access-date=2026-05-29}}</ref>

